revision.text:
'''新田原'''
* 新田原（しんでんばる） - [[福岡県]][[行橋市]]大字道場寺付近の通称。 ** [[新田原駅]]（しんでんばるえき） - 福岡県行橋市大字道場寺にある[[九州旅客鉄道]]（JR九州）[[日豊本線]]の駅。近隣に[[航空自衛隊]]の[[築城基地]]があり、しばしば後述の新田原基地と混同される。 * 新田原（にゅうたばる） - [[宮崎県]][[児湯郡]][[新富町]]大字新田にある地区の通称。旧宮崎県児湯郡[[新田村 (宮崎県)|新田村]]（にゅうたそん）字新田原。 ** [[新田原基地]]（にゅうたばるきち） - 宮崎県児湯郡新富町大字新田にある[[航空自衛隊]]の基地。
{{Aimai}}

'''Shindehara''' (新田原)
== List ==
* Shindehara (しんでんはら) - A place name in {{ill|Minamiaizu, Fukushima|ja|南会津町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Minamiaizu District, Fukushima|ja|南会津郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Shindenbaru (しんでんばる) - A commonly used name for an area near {{ill|Dojoji, Yukuhashi, Fukuoka|ja|行橋市道場寺|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yukuhashi, Fukuoka|ja|行橋市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県|12=draft|12=draft}}. ''' {{ill|Shindenbaru Station|ja|新田原駅|12=draft|12=draft}} (しんでんばるえき) - A station on the {{ill|Nippō Main Line|ja|日豊本線|12=draft|12=draft}} operated by {{ill|Kyushu Railway Company|ja|九州旅客鉄道|12=draft|12=draft}} (JR Kyushu), located in Yukuhashi City, Fukuoka Prefecture. The nearby {{ill|Tsuiki Air Base|ja|築城基地|12=draft|12=draft}}, operated by the {{ill|Japan Air Self-Defense Force|ja|航空自衛隊|12=draft|12=draft}}, is often confused with the later-mentioned Nyūtabaru Air Base.
* Shintabaru (しんたばる) - A place name in {{ill|Konagai Town, Isahaya, Nagasaki|ja|諫早市小長井町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Isahaya, Nagasaki|ja|諫早市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県|12=draft|12=draft}}. Specifically, {{ill|Shintabaru, Konagai Town|ja|小長井町新田原|12=draft|12=draft}}, formerly part of {{ill|Kitatakaki District, Nagasaki|ja|北高来郡|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* Nyūtabaru (にゅうたばる) - A district name in {{ill|Nyūta, Shintomi, Miyazaki|ja|新富町新田|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Shintomi, Miyazaki|ja|新富町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Koyu District, Miyazaki|ja|児湯郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Miyazaki Prefecture|ja|宮崎県|12=draft|12=draft}}. Formerly part of {{ill|Nyūta Village, Miyazaki|ja|新田村 (宮崎県)|12=draft|12=draft}} (にゅうたそん), Nyūtabaru neighborhood. ''' {{ill|Nyūtabaru Air Base|ja|新田原基地|12=draft|12=draft}} (にゅうたばるきち) - A {{ill|Japan Air Self-Defense Force|ja|航空自衛隊|12=draft|12=draft}} base located in Nyūta, Shintomi, Miyazaki Prefecture.
* Shindenpara (しんでんぱら, generally read as しんでんはら) - An unofficial name used to describe the area near Tobu Bus stops located in Higashi 3-chome and Otsuka-cho 12, along Prefectural Route 51 (Ichikawa-Kashiwa Line) in {{ill|Kashiwa, Chiba|ja|柏市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is roughly a 17-minute walk from the east exit of Kashiwa Station. Although there is no official place name "Shindenpara," the area is commonly known as a branching point from Kashiwa Station toward Masuo and Shonan.
== References == * {{ill|Kadokawa Japan Place Name Dictionary|ja|角川日本地名大辞典|12=draft|12=draft}} (various volumes). == See Also == * {{Intitle}} * {{Prefix}} * {{ill|Tahara (disambiguation)|ja|田原 (曖昧さ回避)|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Harada (disambiguation)|ja|原田 (曖昧さ回避)|12=draft|12=draft}}
