'''Shindehara''' (新田原)

== List ==

* Shindehara (しんでんはら) - A place name in {{ill|Minamiaizu, Fukushima|ja|南会津町}}, {{ill|Minamiaizu District, Fukushima|ja|南会津郡}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}}.

* Shindenbaru (しんでんばる) - A commonly used name for an area near {{ill|Dojoji, Yukuhashi, Fukuoka|ja|行橋市道場寺}}, {{ill|Yukuhashi, Fukuoka|ja|行橋市}}, {{ill|Fukuoka Prefecture|ja|福岡県}}.
  ''' {{ill|Shindenbaru Station|ja|新田原駅}} (しんでんばるえき) - A station on the {{ill|Nippō Main Line|ja|日豊本線}} operated by {{ill|Kyushu Railway Company|ja|九州旅客鉄道}} (JR Kyushu), located in Yukuhashi City, Fukuoka Prefecture. The nearby {{ill|Tsuiki Air Base|ja|築城基地}}, operated by the {{ill|Japan Air Self-Defense Force|ja|航空自衛隊}}, is often confused with the later-mentioned Nyūtabaru Air Base.

* Shintabaru (しんたばる) - A place name in {{ill|Konagai Town, Isahaya, Nagasaki|ja|諫早市小長井町}}, {{ill|Isahaya, Nagasaki|ja|諫早市}}, {{ill|Nagasaki Prefecture|ja|長崎県}}. Specifically, {{ill|Shintabaru, Konagai Town|ja|小長井町新田原}}, formerly part of {{ill|Kitatakaki District, Nagasaki|ja|北高来郡}}.

* Nyūtabaru (にゅうたばる) - A district name in {{ill|Nyūta, Shintomi, Miyazaki|ja|新富町新田}}, {{ill|Shintomi, Miyazaki|ja|新富町}}, {{ill|Koyu District, Miyazaki|ja|児湯郡}}, {{ill|Miyazaki Prefecture|ja|宮崎県}}. Formerly part of {{ill|Nyūta Village, Miyazaki|ja|新田村 (宮崎県)}} (にゅうたそん), Nyūtabaru neighborhood.
  ''' {{ill|Nyūtabaru Air Base|ja|新田原基地}} (にゅうたばるきち) - A {{ill|Japan Air Self-Defense Force|ja|航空自衛隊}} base located in Nyūta, Shintomi, Miyazaki Prefecture.

* Shindenpara (しんでんぱら, generally read as しんでんはら) - An unofficial name used to describe the area near Tobu Bus stops located in Higashi 3-chome and Otsuka-cho 12, along Prefectural Route 51 (Ichikawa-Kashiwa Line) in {{ill|Kashiwa, Chiba|ja|柏市}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県}}. It is roughly a 17-minute walk from the east exit of Kashiwa Station. Although there is no official place name "Shindenpara," the area is commonly known as a branching point from Kashiwa Station toward Masuo and Shonan.

